Caroline Adler has been promoted to the role of Special Assistant to the President and Communications Director to the First Lady, replacing Maria Cristina “MC” González Noguera who will be leaving her role on May 1st. Mrs. Obama expressed her gratitude for MC's work and announced her excitement for Caroline's promotion. MC González Noguera also expressed her gratitude for the opportunity to serve the First Lady and the President and passed the torch to Caroline Adler, whom she believes will be an incredible leader and partner to the First Lady. Caroline Adler has been serving as Deputy Communications Director to the First Lady and has been leading the communications strategy for various initiatives such as Joining Forces, Reach Higher, and Let Girls Learn. She has previously worked at the Department of State under Secretary Clinton and is a graduate of Harvard University.